#: front-page.php:305
msgid "Pick the topics you care about and we'll show you the meetings that matter."
msgstr "Filifili autu e te fiafia i ai ma o le a faʻaalia atu fonotaga tāua."

#: front-page.php:320
msgid "Civic tools"
msgstr "Meafaigaluega faitulafono"

#: front-page.php:322
msgid "What you can do on Civi.Me"
msgstr "O mea e mafai ona e faia i Civi.Me"

#: front-page.php:363
#: front-page.php:403
#: front-page.php:443
#: front-page.php:487
msgid "Live"
msgstr "Ola"

#: front-page.php:365
msgid "Browse Meetings"
msgstr "Suesue Fonotaga"

#: front-page.php:368
msgid "All public meetings — boards, commissions, and councils — in one calendar. Filter by topic, council, or date. AI-generated summaries explain what's on the agenda."
msgstr "Fonotaga lautele uma — poloaiga, komisiona, ma fono — i se kalena e tasi. Fasi i autu, fono, po o aso. Faʻamatalaga aotelega faʻatupu-AI e faʻamaoti ai mea i le polokalame."

#: front-page.php:405
msgid "Council Profiles"
msgstr "Faʻamatalaga Fono"

#: front-page.php:408
msgid "Learn what each board and commission actually does — in plain language. See who sits on the board, upcoming meetings, open seats, and how to participate."
msgstr "Aʻo le mea e faia moni ai e poloaiga ma komisiona uma — i upu māmā. Vaai po o ai e nofo i le poloaiga, fonotaga o loʻo sau, nofoa tatala, ma le auala e auai ai."

#: front-page.php:445
msgid "Get Alerts"
msgstr "Maua Laʻasaga"

#: front-page.php:448
msgid "Subscribe to topics or specific councils. Get email alerts when meetings are scheduled — before it's too late to participate."
msgstr "Saini i autu pe fono faʻapitoa. Maua laʻasaga imeli pe a faatulagaina fonotaga — aʻo leʻi umi ona auai."

#: front-page.php:489
msgid "Guides & Compliance"
msgstr "Taitaiga ma Usitaiga"

#: front-page.php:492
msgid "Step-by-step civic action guides plus compliance tools for agencies — Sunshine Law, public records, accessibility, and public participation best practices."
msgstr "Taitaiga galuega faitulafono laasaga-i-laasaga ma meafaigaluega usitaiga mo ofisa — Tulafono Sunshine, faʻamaoniga lautele, avanoa, ma uiga sili ona lelei o auai lautele."

#: front-page.php:511
msgid "What we believe"
msgstr "Le mea tatou te talitonu i ai"

#: front-page.php:513
msgid "Information access is a community right"
msgstr "O le avanoa i faʻamatalaga o se aia tatau o le nuu"

#: front-page.php:516
msgid "Every resident deserves to know what decisions are being made that affect their community — in language they can understand, at a time when they can still participate."
msgstr "E tatau ona iloa e tagata uma o le nuu ni faaiuga o loʻo faia e aʻafia ai lo latou nuu — i se gagana e malamalama ai, i se taimi e mafai ai pea ona auai."

#: front-page.php:534
msgid "Strictly nonpartisan"
msgstr "E le aiga moni lava"

#: front-page.php:535
msgid "Civi.Me does not endorse candidates, parties, or positions on any issue. We present facts: what a bill does, who submitted it, when the hearing is. We provide tools and templates — never talking points."
msgstr "E le lagolagoina e Civi.Me sui tauva, vaega, pe tulaga i soʻo se mataupu. Tatou te faʻaalia mea moni: le mea e faia e se pili, po o ai na solia, le taimi o le fono faafofoga. Tatou te tuʻuina atu meafaigaluega ma faʻataʻitaʻiga — e lē na'o upu talanoa."

#: front-page.php:549
msgid "Everyone is included — no exceptions"
msgstr "Aofia uma — e leai ni tuusaunoa"

#: front-page.php:550
msgid "We use \"residents\" — not \"citizens.\" We support all 15 languages recognized by Hawaii's Office of Language Access. We build for mobile and include a phone line for people who don't have a smartphone at all."
msgstr "Tatou te faʻaogaina le upu \"tagata o le nuu\" — ae le o \"tagatanuu.\" Tatou te lagolagoina gagana uma e 15 ua aloaia e le Ofisi o Avanoa Gagana o Hawaiʻi. Tatou te fausia mo telefoni ma aofia ai se laina telefoni mo tagata e leai ni telefoni atamai."

#: front-page.php:561
msgid "Cultural respect is not optional"
msgstr "O le faaaloalo i aganuu e le faʻaogā"

#: front-page.php:562
msgid "Native Hawaiian sovereignty is a living issue, not history. We frame civic participation as community engagement — not blind deference to government structures."
msgstr "O le Pule Tutoatasi o Hawaiʻi Amanaʻia o se mataupu ola, ae le o tala faasolopito. Tatou te faʻatulagaina le auai faitulafono e pei o le aʻoaʻoga o le nuu — ae le o le usita faʻalaloʻalo i faiga malo."

#: front-page.php:573
msgid "Open source and community-built"
msgstr "Punaoa tatala ma fausia e le nuu"

#: front-page.php:574
msgid "Civi.Me's code is public on GitHub from day one. Civic infrastructure should be open to inspection, contribution, and community ownership. If we ever make a decision you disagree with, you can see exactly why — and you can help us do better."
msgstr "O le code o Civi.Me ua lautele i GitHub talu mai le aso muamua. E tatau ona tatala le faavae faitulafono mo su'esu'ega, saofaʻaga, ma le pule a le nuu. Afai tatou te faia se faaiuga e te le finafinau i ai, e mafai ona e vaai moni le mafuaaga — ma e mafai ona e fesoasoani ia i matou e fai sili atu."

#: front-page.php:589
msgid "Join us"
msgstr "Auai mai"

#: front-page.php:591
msgid "Help build civic infrastructure for Hawaii"
msgstr "Fesoasoani e fausia faavae faitulafono mo Hawaiʻi"

#: front-page.php:594
msgid "Civi.Me is open source and community-driven. Whether you're a developer, a civic advocate, or just someone who cares — there's a place for you."
msgstr "O Civi.Me o punaoa tatala ma taitaia e le nuu. Pe o oe se tagata atiaʻe, se faigofie faitulafono, pe o se tasi e agaʻi atu — o loʻo iai sau avanoa."

#: front-page.php:607
msgid "View on GitHub"
msgstr "Vaai i GitHub"

#: front-page.php:610
msgid "Get in touch"
msgstr "Faʻafesoʻotaʻi mai"

